Q2a)

visualize(
  exercise, 
  xvar = "HoursExercised", 
  yvar = "Chance_in_percentage_", 
  type = "scatter", 
  nrobs = -1, 
  color = "Ages", 
  check = "line", 
  custom = FALSE
)

result <- correlation(
  exercise, 
  vars = c("HoursExercised", "Chance_in_percentage_")
)
plot(result, nrobs = 1000)

chance = 1.829*hours + 28.721

result <- regress(
  exercise, 
  rvar = "Chance_in_percentage_", 
  evar = "HoursExercised"
)
summary(result)

Q3a)

income = -2161.959*percentage + 90074.378

visualize(
  county_complete_2019, 
  xvar = "poverty_2019", 
  yvar = "median_household_income_2019", 
  type = "scatter", 
  nrobs = 1000, 
  linecol = "blue2", 
  pointcol = "coral2", 
  check = "line", 
  alpha = 0.74, 
  theme = "theme_minimal", 
  labs = list(
    title = "Median Household Income vs % of Population Below Poverty Level", 
    x = "Percentage", 
    y = "Median Income"
  ), 
  custom = FALSE
)

result <- correlation(
  county_complete_2019, 
  vars = c("poverty_2019", "median_household_income_2019")
)
plot(result, nrobs = -1)

result <- regress(
  county_complete_2019, 
  rvar = "median_household_income_2019", 
  evar = "poverty_2019"
)
summary(result)
